<br>
I am lost here, never had one of these before and can't figure out what to do to correct it.  I got a second computer and I am trying to play EQ on both.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fajon>Fajon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warpriest<br>
Prime Nightmare </span><br>  Posts: 139<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/19/03 2:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1577.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.ameritech.net/users/fatjohn/Emblem.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Linksys Router woes</span><hr size=1> Try updating your firmware from the Linksys website.  I use a Lynksys router with no problems.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=beornnfv>BeornnFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Born to Kill... Othmirs</span><br>  Posts: 163<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/19/03 3:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1577.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Linksys Router woes</span><hr size=1> Update your firmware and specify ports for Everquest to use.  You might be able to find info on this at the Everquest forums, or at least a walkthrough as to what settings to use to prevent this from happening.  I used to have the same problem, but now the only time I go LD is when my isp goes down.<br>
<br>
If you cant get it to work shoot me a tell in game and I can try to walk you through it if I'm not busy. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=139650" target="top"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;">Elder Beornn</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.fireandfury.org" target="top"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;">Fire and Fury</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fauxknight>Fauxknight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/19/03 3:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1577.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Linksys Router woes</span><hr size=1> Had the same problems. Updated the firmware, played with the firewall, and specified the ports for eq and everything has worked fine since then. Not sure which particular change solved the problems, since I did them at the same time, but it was one of those things. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chasefv>ChaseFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tradeskills Mod</span><br>  Posts: 235<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/19/03 3:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1577.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Linksys Router woes</span><hr size=1> /agree<br>
<br>
