<br>
C <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=danelikfv>DanelikFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/20/03 11:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1577.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Linksys Router woes</span><hr size=1> I've had a Linksys router for about two years now, and it's been running 99.9% of that time, I've only taken it down to move it, and as said here, update the firmware.   I've found them to be VERY reliable..  Just plug it in, throw it under the desk, and it'll run forever as long as you update the firmware.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mixxibixiebane>Mixxi Bixiebane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 533<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/21/03 12:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1577.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Linksys Router woes</span><hr size=1> Oh! Oh! Be careful how you do this, though. Update the firmware, but don't use the dreaded version 2.45. It causes many routers to lose their minds, and when you call support, they suggest a hard reset, which makes the router unfixable. The next suggestion from support is to get another router. (Which I then had to do, although I added another step to the suggestion and banged my head on the wall a few times.)<br>
<br>
Seriously, they had big problems with 2.45. I've heard that they took it off the update site in the last week or so. I've now updated the new router with 2.44.2 or something similar and had no problems. Just watch out for the dreaded 2.45!<br>
<br>
And I never had any problems with the router in EQ. It was only when I began the beta for a game that will remain nameless that I started loosing connection every 10 minutes.<br>
